description:
Sunnyside in Coorangbong was Ellen White's favourite home. Built from scratch and close to Avondale College, it was the place that many books on Adventism were written, including the majority of Desire of Ages. She thought this would be her last home, but it only ended up being her residence for just over 4 years.

To find out more information about Ellen White's time in Sunnyside visit our website to read through our extended article.
